// Task 4 (trailing comma in call args): `f(,)` — a lone comma with no
// preceding argument — must stay a parse error. The new COMMA-before-RPAREN
// call arms all require a non-empty expression_list/type_call_arg before
// the COMMA (mirrors workarounds.md §5's `{,}` rule for composite
// literals); there is no `LPAREN COMMA RPAREN` arm.
package main
func f(a int) int { return a }
func main() {
	_ = f(,)
}
